  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "The analyzer's versatility is highlighted by its support for both POSIX and Java threads, making it independent of specific programming environments.",
    "It also includes a shared instruction cache analysis algorithm.",
    "The adaptation of the multicore Chronos WCET analyzer [49] for multithreaded environments allows it to handle various parallelism patterns such as fork-join, SPMD, and producer-consumer models.",
    "Evaluations using benchmark programs demonstrate improvements in WCET precision by reducing pessimism from global flow facts.",
    "By leveraging synchronized parallel processes and opportunistic annotations, this analyzer provides more accurate WCET bounds, enhancing schedulability and resource provisioning in real-time systems.Expanding on these advancements, Schuster et al. [50] introduce PragMetis, a source-level annotation language for WCET analysis."
  ],
